  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN Joint-Project to Address Cooking Fuel Needs, Environmental Degradation and Food Security for Populations Affected by the Refugee Crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This programme was conceived to mitigate the environmental, protection, health and social-economic impacts of the Rohingya crisis in Bangladesh. It supports 100,000 Rohingya and 25,000 host community households with cooking fuel (Liquefied Petroleum Gas - LPG), on and off-farm livelihoods. In addition, activities include reforesting 2,000 hectares of land in host communities and stabilizing 500 hectares of vulnerable land terrains in the camps. IOM leads on the distribution of LPG to enhance access to alternative cooking fuel amongst the Rohingya community living in the camps and the host communities in the neighbouring unions to help ease potential tension between refugees and host communities.</narrative>
  </description>
